Note that you also have to call the `translate()` function to set the point to be rotated around, then draw relative to that point.

If you don&#39;t want to use the `rotate()` function, then you&#39;re first going to have to figure out what point to rotate around, and then rotate around that point. Googling &quot;rotate a point around another point&quot; returns a bunch of results, including this Stack Overflow post: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2259476/rotating-a-point-about-another-point-2d

